		<td><b>experimenter board</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've always thought it would be kind of cool to have something like a "general-purpose" PCB for the NES.  Like perfboard with an NES edge connector and possibly a few traces to help out.  An experimenter board.
<br />
<br />Before I always went from a design straight to PCB, but since I have several ideas I want to try out, it's be cool to rewire it and have a board like this to screw around with later on.
<br />
<br />So I was just curious, if anyone else was interested in such a board.  I'll have extras, but in the next few weeks if anyone has any requests for any parts that require special footprints that they'd want to see, let me know and I'll see if I can fit it in.  Probably I'll have it fit in an NES case, but there's no reason I couldn't just make it really huge (if you use sockets might as well forgot about the case anyways).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


